HEADWORD: Bonnyclabber
<hw>Bon"ny*clab`ber</hw> <pr>(-kl⟦acr⟧b`b⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Ir. <ets>bainne</ets>, <ets>baine</ets>, milk + <ets>clabar</ets>
mud, mire.]</ety> <def>Coagulated sour milk; loppered milk; curdled
milk; -- sometimes called simply <altname>clabber</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

